    <div id="seccion2" class="section">
        <h2>More information</h2>
       
<p>What are addictions?</p>
<p>Addictions are compulsive behaviors or dependencies that are hard to control, often leading to negative consequences. Vape addiction, in particular, involves depending on electronic cigarettes or vaping devices, usually due to the nicotine content there is inside it and the feeling people want to get from it. It’s growing in demand, especially among younger people, as vaping is often perceived as less harmful than smoking traditional cigarettes, but it can still lead to significant health risks and psychological dependence.</p>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?si=nplbEXsMk6BCV3Hd&v=6JsIJoC5EGE&feature=youtu.be" target="_blank">
          check video 1.</a>
          <p>Why are they caused?</p>
          <p>To talk about addictions we need to understand their origins. 
              Addictions are caused by a mix of biological, psychological, and environmental factors. Genetics can actually make someone more prone to addiction, while emotional issues and problems can take people to seek out substances as coping mechanisms in order to feel better or obtain a sense of freedom and peace. Environmental influences, such as family and friends' contact, also play a role. Over time, repeated use of substances such as the nicotine found in vapes can condition the brain to seek out that substance or  pleasure or relief..</p>
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?si=DYyTPPse0zTWMwUG&v=HDfSx_Q7_Yk&feature=youtu.be" target="_blank">
  check video 2.</a>
          <p>Why people vape?</p>
          <p> People vape for various reasons, including the variety of flavors they provide, the belief that it's a less harmful alternative to smoking, and the desire for a stress-relieving activity. Some use vaping as a tool to quit smoking traditional cigarettes, while others start to do it as it is “trending” among young people. However, despite these motivations, vaping still carries health risks, particularly due to nicotine addiction and other potentially harmful substances in this devices. We chose this topic as it is an increasing problem nowadays and people just let it be instead of doing something.</p>
  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?si=hB7lquiW9Fo_3snH&v=aasKIDz9ZX4&feature=youtu.be" target="_blank">
 check video 3. </a>
        </div>


